text: * File access permissions are displayed using the Is -l command. The output from the Is -| command shows all permissions for all levels as three groups of three according to the scheme: * owner read (r) owner write (w) owner execute (x) * group read (r) group write (w) group execute (x) * public read (r) public write (w) public execute (x) which are displayed as: -rwxrwxrwx
